### API Testing with VSCode REST Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

# After running `node seed.js`, copy the printed IDs here:
@userId = REPLACE_ME_USER_ID
@roomId = REPLACE_ME_ROOM_ID

### 1. Book a Room (Task 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/book-room
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "roomId": "{{roomId}}"
}

### 2. Get All Bookings (Task 2)
GET {{baseUrl}}/bookings

### 3. Get Bookings by Status (Task 2 Bonus)
GET {{baseUrl}}/bookings?status=confirmed

### 4. Upload an Image (Task 3)
# To test this endpoint via REST Client extension or curl, make sure you provide an image.
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload-image
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="image"; filename="sample.txt"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./README.md
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--
